name: Amanda Knox
summary: Amanda Knox, who was previously convicted and later acquitted of murdering her roommate Meredith Kercher in 2007, has been re-convicted of slander in an Italian court. The charges stem from statements she made during a 2019 television interview, in which she accused an innocent man, Patrick Lumumba, of killing Kercher. Knox maintains her innocence and plans to appeal the verdict. The slander case is separate from the murder trial, and although she was found guilty, she is not expected to return to jail. Despite the re-conviction, Knox remains determined to defend herself and clear her name.

summary: John Blackman, the beloved star of the iconic Australian television show "Hey Hey It's Saturday," has passed away at the age of 76 after a valiant battle with cancer. Blackman, who was known for his infectious laugh and jovial demeanor, brought joy to countless Australian homes for decades. His legacy as a television legend is celebrated by fans, colleagues, and the entertainment industry alike, who have expressed their heartfelt condolences and shared anecdotes of his warm spirit and dedication to making people smile. Tributes have poured in from across the nation, honoring the memory of a true Australian icon who played an integral role in shaping the country's television landscape.

name: The Acolyte
summary: The debut of "The Acolyte," a new "Star Wars" series on Disney+, has received mixed reactions. While some critics have praised it as a refreshing and promising addition to the franchise, others have found it disappointing or even a misfire. The series follows a young woman named Aura as she investigates the disappearance of her Jedi master and uncovers a sinister conspiracy involving the dark side of the Force. While some reviewers have appreciated the show's focus on the Jedi and its exploration of the High Republic era, others have criticized its slow pacing, lackluster characters, and overly complicated plot. Despite the mixed reviews, the show has been compared favorably to the recently acclaimed "Andor" series, suggesting that it could still find a loyal audience among "Star Wars" fans.

After being called upon at the last minute to fill in for injured fullback Billy Slater, Tabuai-Fidow revealed that the team's intense training sessions had prepared them for the unexpected. Tabuai-Fidow's contributions extended beyond scoring, as he also prevented a potential try by New South Wales. His outstanding performance underscores his exceptional talent and solidifies Queensland's lead in the series.
